This paper proposes a new architecture for convolutional neural networks that is designed to be efficient for limited computing power devices. As such, it is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep supervision and efficient gradient flow, which are topics commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed architecture on several image datasets, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
